pesticide.PPE: Long-sleeved shirt and long pants; Chemical resistant gloves made of polyvinyl chloride (PVC) ≥14 mils, nitrile rubber ≥14 mils, or butyl rubber ≥14 mils; Shoes plus socks

Active_Ingredients.name: Prothioconazole
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: Demethylation inhibitor (DMI), triazolinthiones, FRAC Group 3 fungicide

Safety_Information.general_Info: Harmful if swallowed or inhaled. Avoid breathing spray mist. Causes moderate eye irritation. Wash thoroughly with soap and water after handling and before eating, drinking, chewing gum, using tobacco or using the toilet. Avoid contact with eyes or clothing. Wear long-sleeved shirt and long pants, socks and shoes. Remove and wash contaminated clothing before reuse.
Safety_Information.if_In_Eyes: Hold eyes open and rinse slowly and gently with water for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present, after the first 5 minutes, then continue rinsing eye. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_Swallowed: Immediately call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice. Have person sip a glass of water if able to swallow. Do not induce vomiting unless told to do so by a poison control center or doctor. Do not give anything by mouth to an unconscious person.
Safety_Information.if_Inhaled: Move person to fresh air. If person is not breathing, call 911 or an ambulance, then give artificial respiration, preferably by mouth-to-mouth, if possible. Call a poison control center or doctor for further treatment advice.
